review_blob: Quite bitter and heavily carbonated.  Extremely nutty/mapley smell.  Very heavy, but the alcohol is hidden quite well.

Forget a can... Im drinking this beer from a keg right now, and Im reminded of how truely terrible it is.  Very light, typical watery domestic.  A little dry, this beer goes down like Mexican water.  Except for the occasional frat party, avoid this beer.  Happy 4-20!
Smells like my right nut, but goes down smooth.  Leaves a pleasant aftertaste.
Odd odor, but quite a delicious taste.  Leaves a crisp taste behind.
Mild aroma, smooth taste, but a bit tarte on the palate.
One actually has to taste this fresh from an Amsterdam tap to understand how good this beer is.  Drink *cold*!
Bitter, cheap, classic American beer.  There are better ways to get drunk...
If youre in the market for cheap beer, this is the one.  It doesnt taste repulsive and it gets you faded quickly.
